<!-- Architecture -->
<section id="architecture" class="py-20 px-6 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-center mb-4">Architecture</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-500 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-12 text-lg font-light">Multi-stage pipeline from Portuguese source to optimized bytecode, JavaScript, or WebAssembly.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3 text-sm mb-6">
      <div class="bg-pinky-50 border border-pinky-200 rounded-xl px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-pinky-600 shadow-sm">Source (.xs)</div>
      <div class="text-gray-300 text-2xl">&#8594;</div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 shadow-sm"><span class="font-semibold">Lexer</span><br><span class="text-xs text-gray-400">lexer.js</span></div>
      <div class="text-gray-300 text-2xl">&#8594;</div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 shadow-sm"><span class="font-semibold">Parser</span><br><span class="text-xs text-gray-400">parser.js</span></div>
      <div class="text-gray-300 text-2xl">&#8594;</div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl px-5 py-3 text-gray-700 shadow-sm"><span class="font-semibold">Optimizer</span><br><span class="text-xs text-gray-400">opt.js</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Lexer - DFA-Based Tokenization</h4>
        <p>The lexer operates as a deterministic finite automaton scanning left-to-right with one-token lookahead. Multi-word keywords (e.g., <code>SE LIGA SO</code>) are matched by consuming consecutive WORD tokens from the stream and checking a keyword dictionary. Unicode support through full <code>String.codePointAt</code> iteration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Parser - Recursive Descent</h4>
        <p>Hand-written recursive-descent parser producing a typed AST with 40+ node types. Expressions use precedence climbing (for <code>+</code>, <code>*</code>, comparisons) with left-associativity. Implements panic-mode error recovery - on parse error, skips to the next statement boundary and continues reporting.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Optimizer - Multi-Pass Rewriting</h4>
        <p>Runs a series of tree walks: <strong>constant folding</strong> (pre-computes <code>2 + 3 * 5</code> at compile time), <strong>loop unrolling</strong> (up to 8 iterations for fixed-range loops), <strong>integer hinting</strong> (annotates variables as integer-only), <strong>function inlining</strong> (for single-call-site functions under 15 nodes).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Codegen - Three Backends</h4>
        <p><strong>codegen.js</strong>: direct JS with keyword mapping. <strong>codegen_opt.js</strong>: enhanced JS using TypedArrays and COMBINA emission. <strong>codegen_wasm.js</strong>: emits Wasm binary byte-by-byte with internal linker supporting i32/f64 locals, branching, memory, and exports.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

